com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core
Interface Capability

All Superinterfaces:
DeployModelObject
All Known Subinterfaces:
BundleCapability, CommunicationCapability, Service
public interface Capability
extends DeployModelObject

A representation of the model object 'Capability'. Capabilities carry configuration content for their containing Unit.

Capabilities satisify Requirements on other Units. The linking may be direct, using a DependencyLink, or indirect using a UnitLink. A unit will typically provide one or more capabilities. Because the model does not support multiple inheritance, the use of multiple capabilites provides the modeler with a tool to capture different facets of the unit.

Capability instances may restrict the types of links that can be bound to them, directly or indirectly. Typically, dependency capabilities have link type CapabilityLinkTypes.DEPENDENCY, while hosting capabilities have link type CapabilityLinkTypes.ANY to express the fact that even though they are hosting, others may have indirect dependencies on their configuration.

Domain extensions are expected to extend the capability type, providing additional attributes.

The following features are supported:

  • Build Version
  • Link Type
  • Origin

See Also:
CorePackage.getCapability()
